#    $Id: INSTALL,v 1.2 2007/05/16 14:44:05 btmcinnes Exp $ 
##################################################################

-----------------------------------------------------------------

This package has been developed and tested on Linux and Solaris, 
primarily using Perl and the C shell (csh).

-----------------------------------------------------------------

This package REQUIRES that the following software and data set to be 
download and installed. 
More details on how to obtain and install appear below. 

--Programming Languages
Perl (version 5.8.5 or better)

--Additional Packages
WEKA Data-mining package

-----------------------------------------------------------------

##################################################################
#                        Programming Languages
##################################################################

Perl (version 5.8.5 or better)
------------------------------

Perl is freely available at http://www.perl.org. It is very likely that 
you will already have Perl installed if you are using a Unix/Linux based 
system. 

#####################################################################
#                    WEKA Data Mining Package
#####################################################################

Weka is a collection of machine learning algorithms for data mining 
tasks. This package uses Weka's machine learning algorithms to perform 
supervised word sense disambiguation. Weka is freely available at 
http://www.cs.waikato.ac.nz/ml/weka/ 

IMPORTANT:

Once Downloaded the remember to set the environment variable WEKAHOME. 
This is required by Weka as well as our package.

For example:

  # in cshell
  setenv WEKAHOME /home/btmcinnes/weka/weka-3-5-3


  # in bash
  export WEKAHOME=/home/btmcinnes/weka/weka-3-5-3

